claim.claim-text:
1. A plastic shopping bag comprising: 
a pair of registering front and back walls, said walls being secured together along their side and bottom edges and open across at least a portion of their top edges; 
said walls, when pulled apart from each other, defining a space into which articles may be placed; 
at least one of said secured together side edges being gusseted; 
a plastic strip disposed within said at least one gusset, said strip having a first end and a second end and being of a length not greater than a length of the gusseted side edge; 
the first end of said strip being heat sealed to the bottom edge of the bag and the second end of the strip being adhered in the vicinity of the top edges of the bag walls; 
at least a portion of said strip between its first and second ends being detachable from the remainder of the strip and removable from between the portions of the walls defining the gusset.

2. A plastic shopping bag comprising: 
a pair of registering front and back walls, said walls being secured together along their side and bottom edges and open across at least a portion of their top edges; 
said walls, when pulled apart from each other, defining a space into which articles may be placed; 
at least one of said secured together side edges being gusseted; 
a plastic strip disposed along one side of the gusset, said strip having a first end and a second end and being of a length not greater than a length of the gusseted side edge; 
the first end of said strip being heat sealed to the bottom edge of the bag and the second end of the strip being adhered in the vicinity of the top edges of the bag walls; 
at least a portion of said strip between its first and second ends being detachable from the remainder of the strip and removable from the bag walls.

