7. A plastic shopping bag comprising: 
a pair of registering front and back walls, said walls being secured together along their first and second side edges and a bottom edge and open across at least a portion of their top edges; 
said walls, when pulled apart from each other, defining a space into which articles may be placed; 
said secured together first and second side edges being folded inwardly from said front and back walls to form a pair of gussets, said gussets having top and bottom edges; 
said top edges of the front wall, the back wall, and the gussets terminating in an upper seam; 
said bottom edges of the front wall, the back wall, and the gussets terminating in an lower seam, said lower seam being perpendicular to the side edges of the front and back walls; 
a U-shaped cut-out, said U-shaped cut-out being disposed in an upper portion of the bag and commencing at a first point along the upper seam spaced inwardly from said first side edge and extending to a second point along the upper seam spaced inwardly from said second side edge, said cut-out extending downwardly toward the lower seam, thereby forming an open mouth and a pair of bag handles; 
a plastic strip disposed within at least one gusset, said strip having a first end and a second end and being of a length not greater than a length of the gusset; 
said first end of the strip being heat sealed to the lower seam and said second end of the strip being heat sealed to the upper seam; said strip being adhered to the gusset between said first end and said second end; and 
at least a portion of said strip between its first and second ends being detachable from the remainder of the strip and removable from between the portions of the walls defining the gusset.

8. A plastic shopping bag comprising: 
a pair of registering front and back walls, said walls being secured together along their first and second side edges and a bottom edge and open across at least a portion of their top edges; 
said walls, when pulled apart from each other, defining a space into which articles may be placed; 
said secured together first and second side edges being folded inwardly from said front and back walls to form a pair of gussets, said gussets having top and bottom edges; 
said top edges of the front wall, the back wall, and the gussets terminating in an upper seam; 
said bottom edges of the front wall, the back wall, and the gussets terminating in an lower seam, said lower seam being perpendicular to the side edges of the front and back walls; 
a U-shaped cut-out, said U-shaped cut-out being disposed in an upper portion of the bag and commencing at a first point along the upper seam spaced inwardly from said first side edge and extending to a second point along the upper seam spaced inwardly from said second side edge, said cut-out extending downwardly toward the lower seam, thereby forming an open mouth and a pair of bag handles; 
a plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and back walls above at least one gusset, said strip having a first end and a second end and being of a length not greater than a length of the gusset; 
said first end of the strip being heat sealed to the lower seam and said second end of the strip being heat sealed to the upper seam; 
said strip being adhered to one of the front and back walls above at least one gusset between said first end and said second end; and 
at least a portion of said strip between its first and second ends being detachable from the remainder of the strip and removable from one of the walls of the bag.

9. An apparatus for fabricating plastic shopping bags each having closed side and bottom edges, at least one side edge being gusseted, and an open top edge, the at least one gusseted side edge being comprised of an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion in abutment with each other, and a plastic strip disposed between said upper and lower wall portions of the gusseted side edge, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing having a plastic strip disposed in the gusset, in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at the cutting station at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks of a predetermined length; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
and said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset and enclosed plastic strip portion on the first side of the blade; 
a vacuum element on its second side also adjacent said cutting edge and above the upper wall portion of the gusseted side edge; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to the at least one gusset of the tubing; 
said vacuum element being disposed adjacent the portion of the blade edge which, upon the blade being lowered to its second position, cuts through the at least one gusset; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing and abutting plastic strip, at which instant the adjacent area of the upper wall portion of the at least one gusset is momentarily raised from its abutment with the plastic strip; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised upper wall portion of the gusset and the plastic strip when the vacuum element momentarily lifts said upper wall portion; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised portion of the gusset, to compress said raised area of the gusset back to the plane of the remaining portion of the cut blank and against the plastic strip; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily lifts an area of the upper wall portion of the gusset adjacent the second side of the blade, and the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised area of the upper wall portion of the gusset and the cut end of the plastic strip, following which, upon the raising of the blade to its first position, the adhesive receiving upper edge of the gusset is pressed back down against the cut end of the plastic strip to the plane of the remainder of the cut blank.

10. An apparatus for fabricating plastic bags each having an open top edge, at least one gusseted side edge and a plastic strip disposed along one side of the gusseted side edge, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving flattened plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
said tubing being gusseted along at least one side edge and having a plastic strip disposed along one side of the gusset of said at least one side edge; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at pre-selected points along its length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side, said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge and a vacuum element on its second side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset and the plastic strip disposed along one side of the gusseted side edge on the first side of the blade; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to the at least one gusset of the tubing; 
said vacuum element being disposed adjacent the portion of the blade edge which, upon the blade being lowered to its second position, cuts through the at least one gusset and abutting plastic strip; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing and abutting plastic strip, at which instant the cut end of the plastic strip is momentarily raised from the side edge of the at least one gusset; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised plastic strip and the side of the gusset when the vacuum element raises said strip; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised portion of the strip, to compress said raised upper cut end of the strip to the plane of the cut blank; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing and the plastic strip on the first side of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily raises the cut end of the plastic strip adjacent the second side of the blade, at which instant, the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised cut end of the strip and the side of the gusset, following which, upon the lifting of the blade to its first position, the adhesive receiving cut end of the plastic strip is pressed back down to the plane of the cut blank.

11. An apparatus for fabricating plastic shopping bags each having closed side and bottom edges, at least one side edge being gusseted, and an open top edge, the at least one gusseted side edge being comprised of an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion in abutment with each other, and a plastic strip disposed between said upper and lower wall portions of the gusseted side edge, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at the cutting station at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks of a predetermined length; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
and said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset on the first side of the blade; 
a vacuum element on its second side also adjacent said cutting edge and above the upper wall portion of the gusseted side edge; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to the at least one gusset of the tubing; 
said vacuum element being disposed adjacent the portion of the blade edge which, upon the blade being lowered to its second position, cuts through the tubing; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing at which instant the adjacent area of the upper wall portion of the at least one gusset is momentarily raised from its abutment with the lower wall portion of the gusset; 
means for inserting a plastic strip of predetermined length into the gusset; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive in at least two locations between the raised upper wall portion of the gusset and the plastic strip when the vacuum element momentarily lifts said upper wall portion; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised upper portion of the gusset, to compress said raised area of the gusset back to the plane of the remaining portion of the cut blank and against the plastic strip; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily lifts an area of the upper portion of the gusset adjacent the second side of the blade, a plastic strip of predetermined length is inserted into the gusset and the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised area of the portion of the gusset and at least two locations on the plastic strip, following which, upon the raising of the blade to its first position, the adhesive receiving upper edge of the gusset is pressed back down against the plastic strip to the plane of the remainder of the cut blank.

12. An apparatus for fabricating plastic bags each having an open top edge, at least one gusseted side edge and a plastic strip disposed along one side of the gusseted side edge, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving flattened plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
said tubing being gusseted along at least one side edge; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at pre-selected points along its length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side, said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset on the first side of the blade; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive at at least two locations along one side of the gusseted side edge of the bag blank; 
means for disposing a plastic strip of a predetermined length along one side of the gusseted side edge of the bag blank over the discharged adhesive; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the plastic strip, to compress said strip to the gusseted side edge of the bag blank; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade, the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive at at least two locations along one side of the gusseted side edge of the bag blank, following which, a plastic strip of a predetermined length is disposed along one side of the gusseted side edge of the bag blank over the discharged adhesive, and the plastic strip is compressed to the gusseted side edge of the bag blank.

13. An apparatus for fabricating plastic bags each having an open top edge and a plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving flattened plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
said tubing having a plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at pre-selected points along its length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side, said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge and a vacuum element on its second side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing and the plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges on the first side of the blade; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to the side edges of the tubing; 
said vacuum element being disposed adjacent the portion of the blade edge which, upon the blade being lowered to its second position, cuts through the tubing and abutting plastic strip; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing and abutting plastic strip, at which instant the cut end of the plastic strip is momentarily raised from either of the front and back walls; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised plastic strip and either of the front and back walls when the vacuum element raises said strip; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised portion of the strip, to compress said raised upper cut end of the strip to the plane of the cut blank; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing and the plastic strip on the first side of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily raises the cut end of the plastic strip adjacent the second side of the blade, at which instant, the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised cut end of the strip and either of the front and back walls, following which, upon the lifting of the blade to its first position, the adhesive receiving cut end of the plastic strip is pressed back down to the plane of the cut blank.

14. An apparatus for fabricating plastic bags each having an open top edge and a plastic strip upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving flattened plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at pre-selected points along its length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side, said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive at at least two locations upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges of the bag blank; 
means for disposing a plastic strip of a predetermined length upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges of the bag blank over the discharged adhesive; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the plastic strip, to compress said strip to either of the front and back walls of the bag blank; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade, the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive at at least two locations upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges of the bag blank, following which, a plastic strip of a predetermined length is disposed upon at least one of the front and back walls between the side edges of the bag blank over the discharged adhesive, and the plastic strip is compressed to the wall of the bag blank.

15. An apparatus for fabricating plastic shopping bags each having closed side and bottom edges, first and second side gussets, a partially open top edge, and a pair of bag handles terminating at the top edge, the gussets being comprised of an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion in abutment with each other, and a plastic strip disposed between said upper and lower wall portions of at least one gusset, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing having a plastic strip disposed in at least one of the gussets, in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at the cutting station at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks of a predetermined length; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
and said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying first and second heating elements on its first and second sides adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating elements serving to heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag including its gussets and enclosed plastic strip portion on the first and second sides of the blade; 
a vacuum element disposed on the second side of the blade and spaced from said second heating element and above the upper wall portion of the gusseted side edge; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to at least one gusset of the tubing; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing and abutting plastic strip, at which instant the adjacent area of the upper wall portion of the gusset is momentarily raised from its abutment with the plastic strip; 
means for activating the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive in at least two locations between the raised upper wall portion of the gusset and the plastic strip when the vacuum element momentarily lifts said upper wall portion; 
means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised upper portion of the gusset, to compress said raised area of the gusset back to the plane of the remaining portion of the cut blank and against the plastic strip; 
means for cutting a U-shaped cut-out commencing at the sealed top edge of the bag blank and extending downwardly toward the bottom edge of the blank; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating elements on the first and second sides of the blade heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag and the plastic strip on the first and second sides of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily lifts an area of the upper portion of the gusset spaced from the second side of the blade, and the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive in at least two locations between the raised area of the upper portion of the gusset and a portion of the plastic strip between its first and second end, following which, upon the raising of the blade to its first position, the raised upper portion of the gusset is pressed back down against the plastic strip to the plane of the cut blank, a U-shaped cut-out is then cut in the bag blank commencing at the sealed top edge and extending downwardly toward the bottom edge, thus yielding an open mouth and a pair of bag handles.

16. An apparatus for fabricating plastic shopping bags each having front and rear outer surfaces, closed side and bottom edges, first and second side gussets, a partially open top edge, and a pair of bag handles terminating at the top edge, the gussets being comprised of an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion in abutment with each other, and a plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and rear outer surfaces above at least one gusset, said apparatus comprising: 
means for moving extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing having a plastic strip disposed upon at least one of the front and rear outer surfaces above at least one gusset, in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at the cutting station at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks of a predetermined length; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
and said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying first and second heating elements on its first and second sides adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating elements serving to heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag including its gussets and the plastic strip on the first and second sides of the blade; 
a vacuum element disposed on the second side of the blade and spaced from said second heating element and above the upper wall portion of the gusseted side edge; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to at least one gusset of the tubing; 
an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade carrying the vacuum element; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing and abutting plastic strip, at which instant a portion of the plastic strip disposed above the gusset is momentarily raised from its abutment with either of the front and rear outer surfaces; 
