whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating elements on the first and second sides of the blade heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag and the plastic strip on the first and second sides of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily lifts a portion of the plastic strip spaced from the second side of the blade, and the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive in at least two locations between the raised portion of the plastic strip between its first and second end and either of the front and rear outer surfaces, following which, upon the raising of the blade to its first position, the raised portion of the plastic strip is pressed back down to the plane of the cut blank, a U-shaped cutout is then cut in the bag blank commencing at the sealed top edge and extending downwardly toward the bottom edge, thus yielding an open mouth and a pair of bag handles.

17. A method of fabricating plastic bags each having an open top edge, at least one gusseted side edge and a plastic strip disposed within the gusseted side edge, said method comprising the steps of: 
providing extruded plastic tubing, said tubing moving in a first direction and being flattened and gusseted along at least one side edge; 
providing a plastic strip disposed within the gusset of said at least one side edge, said gusset being defined by an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion; 
providing a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
providing a blade with a cutting edge in said cutting station for cutting the gusseted tubing and the plastic strip transversely at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent its cutting edge and a vacuum element on its second side also adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset and enclosed plastic strip portion on the first side of the blade; 
said vacuum element, when the blade is lowered to its second position, extending to the at least one gusset of the tubing; 
said vacuum element being disposed adjacent the portion of the blade edge which, upon the blade being lowered to its second position, cuts through the tubing; 
providing an adhesive injector disposed adjacent the side edge of the blade and proximate to the portion of the blade edge carrying the vacuum element; 
moving said gusseted plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into said cutting station; 
dropping the blade from its first position to its second position to effect cutting the tubing along a first pre-selected transverse line on the tubing; 
heat sealing the cut edge of the tubing including its gusset and enclosed plastic strip portion on the first side of the blade; 
producing a vacuum in the vacuum element when the blade is moved to its second position to cut the tubing; at which point, the upper wall portion of the at least one gusset on the second side of the blade is momentarily raised by the vacuum element from its abutment with the plastic strip; 
causing the adhesive injector momentarily to discharge a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised upper wall portion of the gusset and the plastic strip when the vacuum element lifts said upper wall portion; 
providing means adjacent the first side of the blade and in line with the raised upper wall portion of the gusset, to compress said raised upper wall portion back to the plane of the remaining portion of the cut blank and against the plastic strip; and 
whereby, when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing and the plastic strip on the first side of the blade, and the vacuum element on the second side of the blade momentarily lifts an area of the upper portion of the gusset adjacent the edge of the second side of the blade, and the adhesive injector discharges a pre-selected quantity of adhesive between the raised area of the upper portion of the gusset and the cut end of the plastic strip, following which, upon the raising of the blade to its first position, the adhesive receiving upper edge of the gusset is pressed back down against the cut end of the plastic strip to the plane of the remainder of the cut blank.

