19. A method for disposing a plastic strip, such as one or a series of coupons or advertisements, within at least one gusset of a plastic shopping bag formed of front and back walls secured along at least their side and bottom edges with at least one of its side edges being gusseted, and securing the ends of said plastic strip within said gusset, said method comprising the steps of: 
extruding a pre-selected plastic composition into a tube; 
flattening said tube by passing it between a first pair of rollers; 
moving the flattened tube in a first direction into a gusseting station where at least one side edge of the flattened tube is pressed inwardly between the pair of opposed front and back walls to separate said walls temporarily to form an open gusset of a first predetermined width along said side edge of said flattened tube; 
continuing to move the flattened tube in said first direction with said walls still temporarily spaced apart; 
providing a series of spots of adhesive on the inside of one of the spaced apart walls, said spots being disposed at a second predetermined distance from each other; 
providing a second roller disposed adjacent the spaced apart walls at a 45 degree angle to the first direction; 
providing a roll of plastic strip having a width not greater than said first predetermined width; 
feeding the plastic strip from said roll in a second direction transverse to the first direction onto said second roller, thereby to be redirected to said first direction, and inserted between the spaced apart walls defining the gusset, and in contact with each adhesive spot; 
cutting the plastic strip as it moves along with the gusset into predetermined lengths; 
causing the tube to be reflattened and the spaced apart walls defining the gusset to be closed about the cut strip lengths by passing them between a third pair of rollers downstream of the entry of the strip between said walls, thereby adhesively securing the cut strip lengths within the gusset at each point where a spot of adhesive has been deposited; and 
cutting the flattened gusseted tube into a series of blanks for further processing into bags.

