means for moving flattened plastic tubing in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at pre-selected points along its length to produce the series of blanks; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side, said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying a heating element on its first side adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating element serving to heat seal the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade; and 
whereby, when the plastic strip material is disposed upon either of the front and back walls between the side edges and the plastic strip material is compressed against the tubing and the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating element on the first side of the blade heat-seals the cut edge of the tubing on the first side of the blade, leaving an openable bag mouth on the second side of the blade, the plastic strip material will be adhered to either of the front and back walls.

31. An apparatus for fabricating plastic shopping bags each having closed side and bottom edges, first and second side gussets, a partially open top edge, and a pair of bag handles terminating at the top edge, the gussets being comprised of an upper wall portion and a lower wall portion in abutment with each other, and a plastic strip disposed between said upper and lower wall portions of at least one gusset, said apparatus comprising: 
a roll of plastic strip material, said strip material having parallel first and second side edges and being mounted in an unwind stand; 
means for unrolling said roll of plastic strip material from said unwind stand; 
a cold adhesive applicator; said applicator being disposed to apply either of a continuous and non-continuous bead of cold adhesive between the first and second side edges of said plastic strip material; 
means for activating said cold adhesive applicator as said plastic strip material is unrolled from said unwind stand; 
means for opening a gusset in extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing and feeding said plastic strip material with applied cold adhesive into said gusset; 
means for closing said gusset with said plastic strip material disposed therein and compressing said plastic strip material against said upper wall portion and said lower wall portion of said gusset, thereby adhering said strip material to either of said upper and lower wall portions; 
means for moving extruded flattened and gusseted plastic tubing having plastic strip material disposed in at least one of the gussets, in a horizontal plane into a cutting station, said station having a horizontal planar blade receiving area over which the flattened tubing is moved to be cut into a series of rectangular blanks; 
a blade for cutting the tubing transversely at the cutting station at pre-selected points along the tubing length to produce the series of blanks of a predetermined length; 
said blade being reciprocatable between a first upper poised position, and a second lower cutting position on said planar blade receiving area; 
and said blade being of a length at least as great as the width of the gusseted tubing; 
said blade having a first side and a second side; 
said blade further having a cutting edge and carrying first and second heating elements on its first and second sides adjacent said cutting edge; 
said heating elements serving to heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag including its gussets and enclosed plastic strip material on the first and second sides of the blade; 
means for reciprocating the blade between the first and second positions to effect cutting of the tubing at said pre-selected points; 
means for cutting a U-shaped cut-out commencing at the sealed top edge of the bag blank and extending downwardly toward the bottom edge of the blank; and 
whereby, when the plastic strip material is disposed in the opened gusset and the gusset is then closed and the upper and lower wall portions compressed against the strip material and when the blade is brought down against the tubing to cut it transversely, the heating elements on the first and second sides of the blade heat seal the cut bottom and top edges of the bag and the plastic strip on the first and second sides of the blade, the plastic strip material will be heat sealed into the top and bottom edges of the bag and the strip material will be adhered within the gusset, a U-shaped cut-out is then cut in the bag blank commencing at the sealed top edge and extending downwardly toward the bottom edge, thus yielding an open mouth and a pair of bag handles.

